text.tspan: Probability that target population individual successfully quits smoking
"My partner is fine with me smoking."
"My colleagues don't approve or disapprove of my smoking."
"I am ashamed of being a smoker."
"Without smoking, I woul feel at a loss."
"For me, smoking is something I do automatically."
"I don't think I can successfully quit smoking in the next month."
"I am able to decline cigarettes even when I experience craving."
"Smoking helps me to make contact with people in bars."
"Smoking helps me relax when I feel stressed."
"For me, it is too late to quit anyway."
"I do not think smoking is a disgusting habit."
It is never too late to quit.
For methods to be able to influence (sub-)determinants,
their applications must satisfy the methods' parameters for effectiveness
For each sub-determinant, methods able to change that sub-determinant can be selected using psychological theory,
by first determining of which determinant the sub-determinant is a part, and then identifying methods for that determinant
